<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 182/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from">Colonel E. M.
                                    House</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-10T19:00:00+00:00">December 10, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 8, 5 p.m., serial number 149 [<hi rend="italic">152?</hi>]
                            from the Department, December 9, 9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.?</hi>]<note n="20" xml:id="d335fn20">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                            </note> answering my 233.<note n="21" xml:id="d335fn21">Forwarded to the
                                Secretary of State as the Department’s No. 7, Dec. 7,. 1918, 11
                                a.m., <ref target="#pg_340">p. 340</ref>.</note> Secret for the
                            President. After sending you my number 233, I concluded that it would be
                            best simply to advise <persName>Lord Derby</persName> that I had
                            communicated summary of these proceedings to you. I have not committed
                            you to any of the resolutions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>